Explanation

“In Apache Spark, schema inference is the process by which Spark automatically determines the structure (column names and data types) of a dataset when 
reading data, instead of requiring the user to define it manually.”

Code
df = spark.read.csv("file:/tmp/orders.csv", header=True, inferSchema=True)

df.printSchema()

4..
In Apache Spark, a schema can be defined manually using StructType and StructField, where you explicitly specify column names, data types, and nullability, avoiding the overhead and inconsistency of schema inference.”

Code
from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType

schema = StructType([
    StructField("order_id", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("customer_id", IntegerType(), True),
    StructField("amount", IntegerType(), True)
])

df = spark.read.csv("file:/tmp/orders.csv", header=True, schema=schema)

df.printSchema()
df.show()

