select vs selectExpr
Explanation

“In Apache Spark, select is used to choose columns and apply column-based expressions using the DataFrame API,
whereas selectExpr allows selecting columns using SQL expressions as strings, enabling more complex transformations in a concise way.”

Code
✔ Using select (Column API)
from pyspark.sql.functions import col

df.select(
    col("name"),
    col("age"),
    (col("age") + 10).alias("age_plus_10")
).show()
✔ Using selectExpr (SQL style)
df.selectExpr(
    "name",
    "age",
    "age + 10 as age_plus_10"
).show()

