🔹 alias
Explanation

“alias is used to rename a column or DataFrame temporarily, often used in joins or expressions for readability and disambiguation.”

Code
df.select(col("age").alias("user_age")).show()

df1 = df.alias("a")
df2 = df.alias("b")

