🔹 Column Expression
Explanation

“A column expression in Spark represents a transformation or computation applied to a column using the DataFrame API.”

Code
from pyspark.sql.functions import col

df.select((col("age") * 2).alias("double_age")).show()


11.
🔹 Handling Null Values
Explanation

“In Apache Spark, null values can be handled using functions like drop, fill, and replace, allowing you to remove or substitute missing data based on business requirements.”

Code
✔ Drop nulls
df.dropna().show()

df.dropna(subset=["age"]).show()
✔ Fill nulls
df.fillna({"age": 0, "name": "unknown"}).show()
✔ Replace values
df.replace({None: "N/A"}).show()

