🔹 explode Function
Explanation

“explode is used to transform an array or map column into multiple rows, effectively flattening nested data structures.”

Code
from pyspark.sql.functions import explode

data = [("Alice", ["math", "science"]), ("Bob", ["english"])]
df = spark.createDataFrame(data, ["name", "subjects"])

df.select("name", explode("subjects").alias("subject")).show()
Output Concept
Alice → math  
Alice → science  
Bob → english  

13..

“In Apache Spark, pivot transforms unique values from one column into multiple columns and applies aggregation on another column.”

🧠 Think Like This (Real Understanding)

👉 Pivot = Rows → Columns + Aggregation

🔍 Example (Step-by-step)
📊 Original Data
name | year | sales
A    | 2023 | 100
A    | 2024 | 200
B    | 2023 | 150
💻 Code
df.groupBy("name").pivot("year").sum("sales").show()
📊 Output
name | 2023 | 2024
A    | 100  | 200
B    | 150  | null

