🔹 groupBy
Explanation

“groupBy in Apache Spark is used to group rows in a DataFrame based on one or more columns, enabling aggregation operations on each group.”

Code
df.groupBy("name").sum("sales").show()

15..
🔹 agg
Explanation

“agg is used to perform multiple aggregate functions on grouped data, allowing flexible and efficient aggregation operations in a single step.”

Code
from pyspark.sql.functions import sum, avg

df.groupBy("name").agg(
    sum("sales").alias("total_sales"),
    avg("sales").alias("avg_sales")
).show()

